execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-navier-stokes-learnings.md:22:4. **Killing dead ends immediately.** The C(F₄) direction was killed in exploration 003 via the exact algebraic identity. No time wasted on further investigation. **Always check for algebraic identities behind empirical correlations before making them a strategy direction.** This was knowable before Strategy-002 was designed — a 3-line calculation. The lesson: missionary should verify key empirical findings computationally before building a strategy around them.
